HEADWORD: Diœciously
<hw>Di*⟦oe⟧"cious*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>In a
di⟦oe⟧cious manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Di⟦oe⟧ciously hermaphrodite</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>,
<cd>having flowers structurally perfect, but practically di⟦oe⟧cious, --
those on one plant producing no pollen, and those on another no
ovules.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dioeciousness</ent>⟦br⟧
